Fondsbevillinger - støtte fra Region Halland, til vores residency i forbindelsen med koncerterne i London.  Vores ansøgning var oprindelig til at spille på Cafe Oto, plus en koncert i Bristol og en i Manchester. Det endt med at vores koncert i Manchester blev udskudt til Februar 2024. Så tog vi beslutningen til at spille på NTS Radio i London i stedet for Bristol, hvor vi kunne nå en større publikum i gennem NTSs udsendelse.   Fordi vi blev i London, så var vores udgifter mindre, og så skulle vi ikke bruge så meget fra Region Halland's fond.

En uge før projektets start skete der desværre et uheld i Rasmus familie, der gjorde at han ikke kunne deltage i projektet. Efter aftale med Thinh fra Art Music Denmark ville vi gennemføre projektet uden Rasmus, da det ellers ville skubbe alle deadlines for det samlede projektet og dermed influere de kommende værker. Derfor er punktet for overnatning slettet, da vi aflyste hotellet og Sanna i stedet overnattede hos Oskar under projekts forløb. Det er dermed kun Sannas flybillet, vi ønsker refunderet. The Honorar being paid to the artist is being paid out of the pocket of PAKK Collective/Flemming Valmundsson, who is also the one who applied for AMD on the artist's behalf (as he is a foreign resident).   The Fondsbevillinger are from 2 grants, Goethe Institute in Germany (for the artist's stay during the international workshop and related costs), and AMD (for the international travel) . Goethe wills 730 EUR (ca. 5400 DKK) and AMD 5200 DKK.  To simplify and separate numbers in the different cases, the "Samlet honorar" now only includes the honorar to the artist in question, MICHAELBRAILEY. In the application, this number included the honorar being paid to the performing artists, PAKK Collective, as well. This change will explain the huge change, from the original application, in that budget line.

The project, and the budget numbers related to it (especially the Fondsbevillinger), spans two separate concerts. One of them in Denmark, the other in Iceland. The huge overskud apparent in the budget in your form above this text box stems from the fact that I declare all of the income we received in the project, not only the amount(s) that relate to the concert which took place abroad. If I were to do so, that would mean some overly complex calculations and divisions of what costs pertained to which concert, and how to split the costs of the workload between the two concerts. For transparency's sake, I lay it all up here, in this way.  This is probably suboptimal and unclear for your books. If it is, then please contact me and we will find a way to make my squiggly piece fit into your puzzle.

Comment on the project timeline and report:  We had to delay the residency with Daphne and Nathan because we were waiting for other funding bodies to confirm the full production budget of the piece. Therefore, they were not present in person at the Make Sound residency in Malmö, but did nevertheless participate remotely.  The residency at V7 happened in April and was extremely important for the project, a very successful collaboration. We had 5 full workdays as well as our work-in-progress sharing, which was based on invitation to artists in the music, dance, light art and scenography scene in Copenhagen. After we had a long discussion which was very valuable.   I apologise for sending this report way too late! It was my first time receiving this grant and I didn't realise that it had only 1 month deadline. I hope you can excuse it this time.

Da vi ikke var ansvarlige for at betale honorar for koncerterne, og efter at have bedt den svenske bestyrelse om tallene, men endnu ikke fået svar, har vi afsluttet regnskabet uden at medtage honorartallene  Arrangementet med Snæfríður Björnsdóttir blev aflyst på grund af dødsfald. "Overnatning": Vi fire kvartetmedlemmer indkvarterede os privat de 3 nætter, sov på et billigt hostel én nat (1079 kr.) og fik den sidste nat betalt af Alt R Jazz. Mikko afholdt selv udgifter for hotel, foruden d. 15., som ligeledes blev dækket af Alt R Jazz (resterende 698 kr.). Bemærk også, at langt de fleste internationale transportudgifter er angivet i SEK på kvitteringerne. Eneste undtagelse er Mikkos flybillet, som er i EUR, og som jeg desuden kun betalte halvdelen af.

Andet er fornødenhed: En kop kaffe   Egentlig have jeg tænkt, at projektet først var afsluttet, når jeg vender hjem fra Berlin 1. juli. Udgifter på forplejning, overnatning og lokal transport i DK kan stige.
